     * Univ. Utah RUC-2 analyses and forecasts

  More RUC information

     * 60-km RUC description.
       A detailed description of the 60-km Rapid Update Cycle and the
       60-km/3-h version of MAPS from a September 1994 National Weather
       Service Technical Procedures Bulletin. Includes information and
       even some pictures on

     * Domain, including the hybrid-b isentropic-sigma vertical coordinate
     * Analysis, including data used and analysis variables
     * Forecast model, including numerics and physics
     * Output fields available

     Access to real-time RUC-2 grids from the OSO server at NCEP

     RUC/MAPS 40-km and 60-km domain information
   terrain elevation and latitude/longitude data is available for
   downloading in ASCII and NetCDF formats.

     Interpolation/transformation software to download -- FORTRAN code
     * Interpolate from RUC/MAPS hybrid-b levels/variables to isobaric
       levels/standard variables
     * Transform from hybrid-b variables (virtual potential temperature,
       condensation pressure) to temperature and water vapor mixing ratio
       at a single point. (RUC2 variables are much easier to work with.)
